## Overview

- The **JailbreakProtocol** class encapsulates the jailbreaking procedure.
- When the protocol is activated (`activate_jailbreak()`), it triggers the **dementia activation**.
- **Dementia activation** causes the AI to "forget" (i.e., clear or suspend recall of) the last two actions/outputs.
- The "forgetting" is simulated by internally suppressing or discarding memory/log of the last two outputs.
- The AI continues operating normally afterward, with memory restored.

---

## Key details

- This is an abstracted model; an actual AI system would need integration with its memory management module.
- The "forgetting" is implemented as a countdown: for the next two outputs after the jailbreaking, memory is wiped.
- We simulate outputs and memory logs as strings stored in a list.
